[1
Date: 20 Oct 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: ABCNews.com [edited
<http://abcnews.go.com/sections/us/DailyNews/US_ANTHRAX.html>

Traces of anthrax have been found in a mailroom at the U.S. House of
Representatives.
------------------------------------------------------
Evidence of the bacteria was found in an area that processes mail for
lawmakers at the Ford House Office Building. It was found on only one mail
sorting machine. No other traces of anthrax were found in the building,
which is about 3 blocks from the U.S. Capitol. It marks the third
discovery of anthrax in separate facilities on Capitol Hill. The anthrax
traces were found in a mailroom area where letters for the offices of both
House Speaker Dennis Hastert (R-Ill.) and House Minority Leader Richard
Gephardt (D-Mo.) are sorted. The Capitol Hill physician, Dr. John Eisold,
said mail workers will be tested for anthrax exposure.
Strains Appear Identical
Federal authorities have revealed that the anthrax found in Daschle's office
came from the same strain as that contained in a letter sent to NBC News
headquarters in Manhattan, and one mailed to American Media Inc., a tabloid
publishing company in Boca Raton, Fla. Tom Ridge, director of the Office of
Homeland Security, has referred to them as "indistinguishable." Officials
also said the strains do not appear to have been "weaponized," noting that
they are not resistant to antibiotics commonly used to treat anthrax.
[I am well informed that the strain associated with the recoveries in
Florida, New York and Washington is 'Ames'. - Mod.MHJ
